The HAWKS have arrested nine suspects for alleged corruption
and fraud. Hawks spokesperson Captain Matimba Maluleke said in the
first case, five suspects were arrested, four of which are from the Department
of Economic Development, Environment and Tourism and a police officer from
SAPS-Tubatse were arrested. Maluleke said this happened after allegations that they were
approving and issued liquor licenses without following due procedures. He said the five allegedly colluded between 2012 and 2017
and demanded huge bribes from potential applicants. Maluleke said the second incident saw the arrest of a Deputy
Director at Kutama Senthumule Correctional Centre and his accomplice for
alleged fraud and corruption in Thohoyandou and Polokwane respectively. The Deputy Director allegedly colluded with his accomplice,
a businesswoman from Polokwane. They reportedly overpriced goods exorbitantly in return for
kickbacks. Meanwhile, in Morebenga prosecutor was arrested at his work
place for alleged corruption, fraud and defeating the ends of justice. It is alleged that Serumule approached a suspect and
demanded a bribe in order to make his case vanish. He since appeared at the Magistrateâ€™s Court of Morebeng and
he was released on R1000 bail and his case was postponed to 18 January 2019. 